article.headline: Iona 57, Canisius 52
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Dexter Gray scored a career-high 21 points and grabbed six rebounds as Iona beat Canisius 57-52 Monday night in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. Gray, who was 6-of-14 from the field and 9-of-10 from the foul line, sank a pair of free throws with 3:29 left to put Iona (11-17, 7-9 MAAC) up 50-49. Canisius tied the score when Jovan Robinson sank one of two foul shots before Gray put Iona ahead 52-50, sinking a jumper with 2:19 remaining. Rashon Dwight sealed the win with a 3-pointer with 0:59 left. Greg Logins led Canisius (4-22, 2-14) with 18 points and seven rebounds. Frank Turner scored 15 points and grabbed seven rebounds. Iona sank 15-of-19 from the foul line, but shot just 35.8 percent from the floor (19-for-53) and converted just 4-of-13 3-point shots. Canisius, which dropped its fifth straight, shot 35.2 percent from the field.
